# MTG Trainer environment variables.
# Copy this file to .env.local (which is gitignored) and fill in.
#
# After editing .env.local you must RESTART the dev server (`npm run dev`).
# Vite only reads env vars on boot, not on hot reload.

# ── Anthropic API key (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Get one at https://console.anthropic.com → API keys → Create Key.
# Without a key the app still runs; the AI brain falls back to a local mock
# proposal and the voice parser shows an inline "key missing" message.
#
# SECURITY: this key is bundled into the browser at build time. Acceptable
# for local single-user use; do NOT deploy this app publicly with a real key.
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── OpenAI API key (optional, for higher-quality AI voice) ────────────────
# Get one at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys.
# When set, the TTS provider defaults to OpenAI gpt-4o-mini-tts (much better
# voices than the browser's speechSynthesis, and the model accepts the active
# persona's personalityPrompt as `instructions` for live tone steering).
# Without a key, the app uses the free browser-native TTS instead — both
# are toggleable at runtime from Tweaks → AI voice.
#
# Cost is ~$0.60 per minute of generated audio. AI lines average a few seconds,
# so a typical play session costs cents, not dollars.
#
# SECURITY: same caveat as the Anthropic key — bundled at build time, fine
# for local single-user use, don't deploy publicly.
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=
